        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 11 at 7:29PM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 729 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 3 miles
southwest of Short. This thunderstorm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects.

Locations in or near the path include...
Dora...                           Short...
Uniontown...                      Cedarville...

This includes the following highways,
Interstate 40 in Arkansas near mile marker 0.
Interstate 40 in Oklahoma between mile markers 326 and 328.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
